<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="592" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5508: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-28"><hi rend="italic">October 28,
                                1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received October 29, 10:10
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[From <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at Omsk:]</p>
                        <p>448. October 28th, 5 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Referring to Department’s two telegrams dated October 25th, 5 p.m., and
                            October 25th, 6 p.m.<note n="86" xml:id="d592fn86">Not printed.</note>
                            Soukine informs me that this matter will be taken before the Council of
                            Ministers and he believes it will receive favorable decision.</p>
                        <p>I can confirm <persName corresp="#p_SCH1">Smith</persName>’s viewpoint
                            that there is an improvement already in the attitude of the Russians,
                            especially <persName>Ustrugoff</persName>, who is becoming very
                            conciliatory.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully urge upon the Department advisability of requesting
                                <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> not to withdraw
                            railway inspectors just at this time. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>